    	<div class="mt-4 p-4 md:p-5 rounded-xl bg-zinc-900/45 border border-zinc-800/60 text-base lg:text-xl text-zinc-200 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
    		<strong class="text-zinc-100 font-bold">Explanation:</strong> At this point, I had separately started running in a container on the NAS, <a href="https://tdarr.io/" class="text-blue-400 hover:text-blue-300 underline" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Tdarr</a>, a distributed transcoder to convert the video files to more efficient formats. Although this query failed initially (a warning sign of indicating I was hitting context limits, which I ignored), I retried at 5:52 AM.<br><br>

        The agent parsed logs and hit API endpoints to determine the latest status, all while dragging along the massive 65k-token CSV payload. At 135,000+ input tokens under Gemini 3.5 Flash pricing, a single uncached request cost ~$0.22 (and ~$0.04 even with a warm cache). Because agentic workflows make multiple sequential tool calls per turn, a single status check query requiring 5 tool calls cost anywhere from $0.20 (fully cached) to $1.10 (uncached), rapidly multiplying the billing.
