                <h3 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold text-white group-hover:text-red-400 transition-colors">The Time Bandit</h3>
            </div>
            <h4 class="text-base lg:text-lg font-mono text-zinc-400 font-semibold tracking-wide uppercase">UTC/EDT Time-Zone Desync</h4>
            <p class="text-zinc-200 text-base lg:text-xl leading-relaxed pt-1">
                My logs showed the heavy Tdarr work happening on the night of June 24th, while billing reports showed a massive $44.08 spike on June 25th. This led me to try to debug only requests made on June 25th. However Google Cloud logs are generated in <strong>UTC</strong>. The intensive troubleshooting session that took place late in the evening (EDT) crossed the midnight boundary into UTC time, causing the entire cost to appear on the following day’s billing statement causing me to miss the root cause.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

